  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the beef stew meat and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the red wine, beef broth, tomato paste, allspice, and cinnamon. Stir to combine.",
    "Bring the stew to a boil, then cover and transfer to the oven.",
    "Bake at 300°F for 2 1/2 hours, or until the beef is tender.",
    "While the stew cooks, prepare the nu-kes pickling spice according to the package instructions.",
    "Stir the pickled onion relish into the stew during the last 10 minutes of cooking.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley.",
    "Serve over cornmeal, if desired."
